{
  "text": "After 15 min, excess sperm was removed by flushing eggs retained in a 45 µm wet sieve with FSW. Embryos were reared in 300 L cylindro-conical tanks containing gently aerated FSW maintained at 26 °C [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Larvae were used in experiments five to eight days after fertilisation, corresponding with the onset of feeding [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
